#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:18
msgid "Identify the audience and intended use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:20
msgid ""
"The best documentation starts by knowing the intended readers, their "
"knowledge, and what you expect them to do with the information. "
"Otherwise, you cannot determine the appropriate scope and depth of "
"information to provide, its ideal structure, or the necessary supporting "
"information. The following examples show this principle in action:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:26
msgid ""
"The reader needs to perform a specific task: Tell them how to recognize "
"when the task is necessary and provide the task itself as a list of "
"numbered steps, don’t simply describe the task in general terms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:31
msgid ""
"The reader must understand a concept before they can perform a task: "
"Before the task, tell them about the prerequisite information and provide"
" a link to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:35
msgid ""
"The reader needs to make a decision: Provide the conceptual information "
"necessary to know when to make the decision, the available options, and "
"when to choose one option instead of the other."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:40
msgid ""
"The reader is an administrator but not a SWE: Provide a script, not a "
"link to a code sample in a developer’s guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:43
msgid ""
"The reader needs to extend the features of the product: Provide an "
"example of how to extend the feature, using a simplified scenario for "
"illustration purposes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:47
msgid ""
"The reader needs to understand complex feature relationships: Provide a "
"diagram showing the relationships, rather than writing multiple pages of "
"content that is tedious to read and understand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:51
msgid ""
"The most important thing to avoid is the common mistake of simply giving "
"readers all the information you have, because you are unsure about what "
"information they need."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:55
msgid ""
"If you need help identifying the audience for you content, we are happy "
"to help and answer all your questions during the `Docs Working Group "
"<https://github.com/istio/community/blob/master/WORKING-GROUPS.md#istio-"
"working-groups>`_ biweekly meetings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:61
msgid "Content types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:63
msgid ""
"When you understand the audience and the intended use for the information"
" you provide, you can choose content type that best addresses their "
"needs. To make it easy for you to choose, the following table shows the "
"supported content types, their intended audiences, and the goals each "
"type strives to achieve:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:85
msgid "Content type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:95
msgid "Goals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:105
msgid "Audiences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:127
msgid "Concepts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:137
msgid ""
"Explain some significant aspect of Istio. For example, a concept page "
"describes the configuration model of a feature and explains its "
"functionality. Concept pages don’t include sequences of steps. Instead, "
"provide links to corresponding tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:150
msgid ""
"Readers that want to understand how features work with only basic "
"knowledge of the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:169
msgid "Reference pages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:179
msgid ""
"Provide exhaustive and detailed technical information. Common examples "
"include API parameters, command-line options, configuration settings, and"
" advanced procedures. Reference content is generated from the Istio code "
"base and tested for accuracy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:192
msgid ""
"Readers with advanced and deep technical knowledge of the project that "
"needs specific bits of information to complete advanced tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:211
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:221
msgid ""
"Describe a working and stand-alone example that highlights a set of "
"features, an integration of Istio with other projects, or an end-to-end "
"solution for a use case. Examples must use an existing Istio setup as a "
"starting point. Examples must include an automated test since they are "
"maintained for technical accuracy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:235
msgid ""
"Readers that want to quickly run the example themselves and experiment. "
"Ideally, readers should be able to easily change the example to produce "
"their own solutions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:255
msgid "Tasks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:265
msgid ""
"Shows how to achieve a single goal using Istio features. Tasks contain "
"procedures written as a sequence of steps. Tasks provide minimal "
"explanation of the features, but include links to the concepts that "
"provide the related background and knowledge. Tasks must include "
"automated tests since they are tested and maintained for technical "
"accuracy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:280
msgid "Readers that want to use Istio features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:298
msgid "Setup pages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:308
msgid ""
"Focus on the installation steps needed to complete an Istio deployment. "
"Setup pages must include automated tests since they are tested and "
"maintained for technical accuracy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:320
msgid "New and existing Istio users that want to complete a deployment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:338
msgid "Blog posts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:348
msgid ""
"Focus on Istio or products and technologies related to it. Blog posts "
"fall in one of the following three categories:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:359
msgid ""
"Posts detailing the author’s experience using and configuring Istio, "
"especially those that articulate a novel experience or perspective."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:370
msgid "Posts highlighting Istio features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:380
msgid ""
"Posts detailing how to accomplish a task or fulfill a specific use case "
"using Istio. Unlike Tasks and Examples, the technical accuracy of blog "
"posts is not maintained and tested after publication."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:400
msgid ""
"Readers with a basic understanding of the project who want to learn about"
" it in an anecdotal, experiential, and more informal way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:419
msgid "News entries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:429
msgid ""
"Focus on timely information about Istio and related events. News entries "
"typically announce new releases or upcoming events."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:440
msgid ""
"Readers that want to quickly learn what’s new and what’s happening in the"
" Istio community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:459
msgid "FAQ entries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:469
msgid ""
"Provide quick answers to common questions. Answers don’t introduce any "
"concepts. Instead, they provide practical advice or insights. Answers "
"must link to tasks, concepts, or examples in the documentation for "
"readers to learn more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:482
msgid ""
"Readers with specific questions who are looking for brief answers and "
"resources to learn more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:501
msgid "Operation guides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:511
msgid ""
"Focus on practical solutions that address specific problems encountered "
"while running Istio in a real-world setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:522
msgid ""
"Service mesh operators that want to fix problems or implement solutions "
"for running Istio deployments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:538
msgid "Choosing a title"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:540
msgid ""
"Choose a title for your topic that has the keywords you want search "
"engines to find. All content files in Istio are named ``index.md``, but "
"each content file is within a folder that uses the keywords in the "
"topic’s title, separated by hyphens, all in lowercase. Keep folder names "
"as short as possible to make cross-references easier to create and "
"maintain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:548
msgid "Submit your contribution to GitHub"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:550
msgid ""
"If you are not familiar with GitHub, see our `working with GitHub guide "
"</about/contribute/github>`_ to learn how to submit documentation "
"changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/add-content/index.rst:554
msgid ""
"If you want to learn more about how and when your contributions are "
"published, see the `section on branching </about/contribute/github"
"#branching-strategy>`_ to understand how we use branches and cherry "
"picking to publish our content."
msgstr ""

